snippet.title: Panasonic NN-SD997S microwave
snippet.description: If you're interested in the inverter tech angle, you may be disappointed. But if you don't expect to get artisanal omelets from a microwave, it's still a solid choice for a large, midprice countertop model.

snippet.title: How to switch to Outlook.com using the new Gmail import tool
snippet.description: Switching e-mail providers can be a point of consternation for some people. Outlook.com now has an import tool to make switching from Gmail a worry-free task.

snippet.title: Sony VAIO X505 (Japanese Import)
snippet.description: This extraordinarily light ultraportable might thrill business travelers, but you'd be better off with a U.S. version.

snippet.title: How to import your Google Reader data to Feedly
snippet.description: Feedly now supports importing Google Reader data. If you want to give Feedly a try, we'll show you how to import your subscriptions.

snippet.title: Correction: Easily import Astrid tasks to Any.Do on Android
snippet.description: This story initially said the import feature works on both Android and iOS. It appears to be working only on Android right now.

snippet.title: Easily import Astrid tasks to Any.Do on Android
snippet.description: Worried that all your tasks will disappear if Yahoo shuts down Astrid? Now you can easily migrate them from Astrid to Any.Do.

snippet.title: Clash of Clans on Android: How to import your game from iOS
snippet.description: The popular Clash of Clans game is no longer iOS-only. Here's how Android users can get started. And yes, players can keep their villages in sync across both major platforms.

snippet.title: Instagram video gets import option, works on more Android phones
snippet.description: With the update, video is accessible to more people, as Instagram continues to duke it out with Vine for the crown in mobile video.

snippet.title: How to import your Google Reader data to Digg Reader
snippet.description: If you've saved your Google Reader data, you can start importing the data into alternative readers, like Digg Reader.

snippet.title: Need that iPhone or Android photo fast? Import quickly to Mac with built-in Preview
snippet.description: You don't have to load iPhoto to get pictures off your smartphone and onto your Mac. The Preview app is a quick and easy alternative.
